*"I will turn the darkness into light before them 
and make the rough places smooth."*{Isaiah 42:16}{The inverse function 
undoes what the original function does.}{Mathematical Proverb}

content.solution:
Let $\theta = \sin^{-1}\frac{3}{5}$. Then $\sin\theta = \frac{3}{5}$ and 
$\theta$ is in $\left[-\frac{\pi}{2}, \frac{\pi}{2}\right]$.

Since $\sin\theta = \frac{3}{5} > 0$, the angle $\theta$ is in QI.

Draw a right triangle with $\sin\theta = \frac{\text{opp}}{\text{hyp}} = \frac{3}{5}$:

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.8]
 (0,0) – (4,0) – (4,3) – cycle;
 (3.7,0) – (3.7,0.3) – (4,0.3);

 at (2,0) {$4$};
 at (4,1.5) {$3$};
 at (2,1.7) {$5$};
 at (0.5,0.3) {$\theta$};

 (0.7,0) arc (0:36.87:0.7);
tikzpicture
center

Using the Pythagorean theorem: $\text{adj} = \sqrt{5^2 - 3^2} = \sqrt{16} = 4$.

Therefore:
$$
 \cos\left(\sin^{-1}\frac{3}{5}\right) = \cos\theta = \frac{\text{adj}}{\text{hyp}} = \frac{4}{5}
$$
